OL,3,C'Sadness' as shopkeepers of 40 years
OL,4,Cstruggle to find buyer for their store
OL,6,F"It's a lovely community, there's a
OL,7,Flot of new house building, there's a
OL,8,Flot of well-paid jobs in the vicinity,
OL,9,Fmaybe not immediately, and I just want
OL,10,Fsomebody to recognise Chard and say
OL,11,F'let's come to Chard'."
OL,13,FJohn said: "It feels strange but I'm
OL,14,Flooking forward to the future with
OL,15,Fconfidence but sad in a lot of ways to
OL,16,Fbe leaving."
OL,18,FBarrons now adds to the empty units in
OL,19,FChard. Like so many other towns around
OL,20,Fthe region and the country, retail is
OL,21,Fhard.
