OL,3,C'Sadness' as shopkeepers of 40 years
OL,4,Cstruggle to find buyer for their store
OL,6,FJoe Bray has run Top Togs, and
OL,7,Findependent sports shop, for 27 years.
OL,8,FHe says trade has dramatically dropped
OL,9,Fbecause of online competition and the
OL,10,Ftown centre reflects that.
OL,12,FHe said: "The shops we have got in the
OL,13,Ftown centre tend to be the ones you
OL,14,Fcannot buy stuff on the internet -
OL,15,Fcoffee, hairdressers, I hate to say
OL,16,Fthis but charity shops.
OL,18,F"If I had the choice of going into
OL,19,Fretail again I never would. I wouldn't
OL,20,Frecommend anybody to go into retail at
OL,21,Fthe moment - it's too hard a business."
